com.github.naoghuman.lib.preferences.internal

Class DefaultPreferences

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.naoghuman.lib.preferences.internal.DefaultPreferences

  • public final class DefaultPreferences
extends Object
    The class DefaultPreferences allowed the access to the Properties file DEFAULT_PREFERENCES_FILE.

    The usage from the factory PreferencesFactory is preferred for a simplified access to the methods in this class instead the access through the instantiation with new DefaultPreferences().

    Since:
    0.6.0
    Version:

    • Method Detail

      • application

        public void application()
        Activates the application mode.

        In context from this scope a key, which allows to access or store a value into the Properties, must be unique in the hole application.
        To accomplish this behavior this method adds automatically the prefix from the class DefaultPreferences to the given key.

        Example:

              com.github.naoghuman.lib.preferences.internal.your.key
        Since:
        0.6.0
        See Also:
        key(String), Properties

      • get

        public Boolean get(Boolean def)
        Returnes the Boolean value which is associated with the previouly defined key in key(String).

        If no value is associated with the key then the default value def will returned.
        Is the associated key isn't set previously in key(String) an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

        Hint:
        Be aware about the methods application() and module(java.lang.Class). If one of them isn't used before then the value won't be found (missing prefix from the key).

        Parameters:
        def - the default value if the key doesn't exists.
        Returns:
        the associated value or def.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if (key == NULL).
        NullPointerException - if (def == NULL).
        Since:
        0.6.0
        See Also:
        key(String), DefaultPreferencesValidator.requireNonNull(java.lang.Object), Boolean, IllegalArgumentException, NullPointerException

      • key

        public void key(String key)
        Defines the key which value should returned.

        The key can have the two scopes: application and module

        • Application scope means the key must unique in the hole application.
          Executing the method application() adds automatically the package name from this class DefaultPreferences as prefix to the key.
          Example: com.github.naoghuman.lib.preferences.internal.your.key
        • Module scope means the key must unique in a package scope.
          Executing the method module(Class) adds automatically the package name from the given clazz as prefix to the key.
          Example: the.package.from.the.choosen.class.and.your.key
        Parameters:
        key - the key which value should returned.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if (key.trim() == EMPTY).
        NullPointerException - if (key == NULL).
        Since:
        0.6.0
        See Also:
        application(), module(Class), DefaultPreferencesValidator.requireNonNullAndNotEmpty(java.lang.String), IllegalArgumentException, NullPointerException

      • module

        public void module(Class clazz)
        Activates the module mode.

        In context from this scope a key, which allows to access or store a value into the Properties, must be unique in a package scope.
        To accomplish this behavior this method adds automatically the package name from the clazz to the given key.

        Example:

              the.package.from.the.choosen.class.and.your.key
        Parameters:
        clazz - the package name from this Class defines the module scope.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if (clazz == NULL).
        Since:
        0.6.0
        See Also:
        key(String), DefaultPreferencesValidator.requireNonNull(java.lang.Object), NullPointerException, Properties

      • put

        public void put(Boolean value)
        Saves the Boolean value to the file Preferences.properties.

        Is the associated key isn't set previously in key(String) an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

        Hint:
        Be aware about the methods application() and module(java.lang.Class). If one of them isn't used before then the key havn't the right prefix which means that in the get(..) methods the key won't be found.

        Parameters:
        value - the value which should be saved.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if (key == NULL).
        NullPointerException - if (value == NULL).
        Since:
        0.6.0
        See Also:
        key(String), DefaultPreferencesValidator.requireNonNull(java.lang.Object), Boolean, IllegalArgumentException, NullPointerException
